\section{Modified Weyl gravity}

In the present section we briefly discuss the model of modified Weyl gravity proposed in Ref.~\cite{Dzhunushaliev:2020dom}.

\subsection{Lagrangian}

The Lagrangian of the theory is given by
\begin{equation}
\mathcal{L} = \sqrt{-g}\left[\frac{1}{16\pi G} \left(R + \frac{6}{c^2} \right) - \frac{1}{16\pi G} \left(R + \frac{6}{c^2}\right) \right]~,
\end{equation}
where $G$ is the gravitational constant, $c$ is the speed of light, and $R$ is the Ricci scalar.

\subsection{Equations of motion}

The Einstein field equations in the presence of the cosmological constant $\Lambda$ are
\begin{equation}
G_{\mu\nu} + \Lambda g_{\mu\nu} = 8\pi G T_{\mu\nu}~,
\end{equation}
where $G_{\mu\nu}$ is the Einstein tensor, $T_{\mu\nu}$ is the energy-momentum tensor, and $G$ is the gravitational constant.

